cache and generated IDs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is important to ensure that every feature in the GeoJSON style source, as well as the newly added","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"feature, has a unique ID (or a unique promote ID if in use). Failure to provide unique IDs will result"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in a "},{"code":"map-loading-error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The method allows the user to provide a data ID, which will be returned as the "},{"code":"dataId","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"source-data-loaded"},{"text":" event. However, it’s important to note that multiple partial updates can be queued","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the same GeoJSON source when ongoing source parsing is taking place. In these cases, the partial","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"updates will be applied to the source in batches. Only the data ID provided in the most recent call within"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"each batch will be included in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"source-data-loaded","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" event. If no data ID is provided in the most recent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"call, the data ID in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"source-data-loaded"},{"type":"text","text":"event will be null."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/StyleError","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" if there is a problem removing features from the source."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Throws","style":"note","type":"aside"}],"